org.batfish.symbolic

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.symbolic.Graph

  • public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
    A graph object representing the structure of the network. The graph is built potentially by inferring the link connectivity of the network based on interface ip addresses. Interfaces are abstracted into graph edges, which include a direction. Each graph edge can be mapped to its opposite edge, which may be null, if there is no such edge (e.g., for loopbacks).

    iBGP is modeled as additional "abstract" edges that do not correspond to any concrete edge in the topology.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Graph

        public Graph(IBatfish batfish)
        Create a graph, loading configurations from the given IBatfish.

        Note that, because configurations are not supplied, this Graph will clone the active configurations before use. This avoids side-effects that occur when Graph and other code in this package mutates the configs in the graph.

        For increased, efficiency, use Graph(IBatfish, Map) which will skip the cloning, assuming that the caller has made a defensive copy first.

      • Graph

        public Graph(IBatfish batfish,
             @Nullable
             java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Configuration> configs)
        Create a graph, using the specified configurations.

        Note that the given configs may be mutated during computation; callers are advised to defensively copy them or use Graph(IBatfish), which will do the defensive copy automatically, to avoid this side effect.
